                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 850a.00/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate
                            Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-09T17:00:00+00:19"
                            >January 9, 1919—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 10—9:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>83. My 69, 4th. Note of December 31 referred to therein received today reiterates
                    the facts already communicated to you. The only difference being that the dates
                    of the abrogated conditions [<hi rend="italic">conventions?</hi>] are cited,
                    namely, November 11, 1902 and October 20, 25, 1865. Text follows by pouch.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
